content:
Your code is almost correct, but you need to make sure that the index of `productDetails` array is 1 and not 0. Here's the corrected version:

```
String[] orderData = orderString.split("\\s+");
String[] productDetails = orderData[0].split("–");
int productPrice = priceList.get(productDetails[1]);
int orderPrice = Integer.parseInt(orderData[1]) * productPrice;
```

This code will split the first element of `orderData` by "–" to get the product name and then use that name as a key in `priceList` to get the corresponding price. It also parses the second element of `orderData` (which is assumed to be an integer) into an int and multiplies it by the retrieved product price, storing the result in `orderPrice`.

