```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int height = 5; // replace with your actual height value
        int width = 10; // replace with your actual width value

        int temp = 2 * (height + width);
        System.out.println(temp);

        temp = height * width;
        System.out.println(temp);
    }
}
```

This program first calculates the area of a rectangle by multiplying its length and width, then multiplies it by 2 to get the perimeter. The result is stored in `temp`. Then it prints out `temp`.

Please replace the values of `height` and `width` with your actual measurements.
